# TypeScript Conventions

- Import local modules without `.js` extensions.
- Prefer existing aliases (`@/`, `@/game/`, `@/ui/`, `@/data/`) when they improve clarity.
- Keep class and interface names PascalCase; do not prefix interfaces with `I`.
- Keep functions and variables camelCase; keep constants UPPER_SNAKE_CASE.
- Use `addEventListener` for DOM events and arrow callbacks when `this` binding matters.
- Do not use browser-native `alert()`, `confirm()`, or `prompt()`; use `ModalUtils` / `ToastUtils`.
- For persisted data changes, update `PlayerSaveData` migration and validation paths deliberately.
